vulnerability.name: USN-5300-2
vulnerability.description: USN-5300-1 fixed vulnerabilities in PHP. This update provides the corresponding updates for Ubuntu 18.04 LTS and Ubuntu 20.04 LTS.  Original advisory details:   It was discovered that PHP incorrectly handled certain scripts.  An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service.  (CVE-2015-9253, CVE-2017-8923, CVE-2017-9118, CVE-2017-9120)    It was discovered that PHP incorrectly handled certain inputs.  An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service,  or possibly obtain sensitive information. (CVE-2017-9119)    It was discovered that PHP incorrectly handled certain scripts with XML  parsing functions.  An attacker could possibly use this issue to obtain sensitive information.  (CVE-2021-21707)

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in PHP.
